+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **If you get stuck:** always start by viewing the page source         |
| (Ctrl+U) and reading the JavaScript. The vulnerability is always      |
| visible in the code. Use ZAP to intercept your requests and see       |
| exactly what the server receives and returns. Experiment with unusual |
| characters: \' \" \< \> / ; ( ) --- one of them will break the        |
| context.                                                              |
|                                                                       |
| **The three XSS contexts you will encounter across all six levels:**  |
| (1) between HTML tags --- broken by \< ; (2) inside an HTML attribute |
| --- broken by \" or \' ; (3) inside a JavaScript string --- broken by |
| \' or \" with ; to end the statement. Knowing which context your      |
| input lands in tells you which character to try first.                |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
